theorem Topology.P3_union_dense_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hDenseB : Dense (B : Set X)) :
    Topology.P3 (A ∪ B) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  -- `closure B` is the whole space because `B` is dense.
  have h_closureB : closure (B : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDenseB.closure_eq
  -- Hence `closure (A ∪ B)` is also the whole space.
  have h_closure_union : closure (A ∪ B : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    calc
      closure (A ∪ B : Set X)
          = closure A ∪ closure B := by
            simpa [closure_union]
      _ = closure A ∪ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
            simp [h_closureB]
      _ = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
            simp
  -- Therefore the interior of this closure is the whole space.
  have h_int_union :
      interior (closure (A ∪ B : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closure_union, interior_univ]
  -- Every point belongs to the whole space, so the inclusion holds.
  have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [h_int_union] using this

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_union_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∪ B : Set X)) = interior (closure A ∪ closure B) := by
  -- First inclusion: `interior (closure (A ∪ B)) ⊆ interior (closure A ∪ closure B)`.
  have h₁ :
      interior (closure (A ∪ B : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure A ∪ closure B) := by
    intro x hx
    simpa [closure_union] using hx
  -- Second inclusion: `interior (closure A ∪ closure B) ⊆ interior (closure (A ∪ B))`.
  have h₂ :
      interior (closure A ∪ closure B) ⊆ interior (closure (A ∪ B : Set X)) := by
    intro x hx
    simpa [closure_union] using hx
  -- Combine the inclusions to obtain the desired equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.interior_closure_union_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∪ B : Set X)) = interior (closure A ∪ closure B) := by
  simpa [closure_union]
